.TH "RTCINBOUNDRTPSTREAMSTATS" "3JS" "August 19, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
RTCInboundRtpStreamStats \- RTCInboundRtpStreamStats
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]RTCInboundRtpStreamStats\f[B]\f[R] dictionary of the
WebRTC API is used to report statistics related to the receiving end of
an RTP stream on the local end of the \f[CR]RTCPeerConnection\f[R].
.PP
The statistics can be obtained by iterating the
\f[CR]RTCStatsReport\f[R] returned by
\f[CR]RTCPeerConnection.getStats()\f[R] or
\f[CR]RTCRtpReceiver.getStats()\f[R] until you find a report with the
\f[CR]type\f[R] of \f[CR]inbound\-rtp\f[R].
.SH INSTANCE PROPERTIES
.TP
\f[B]audioLevel\f[R]
A number that indicates the audio level of the received track.
\f[I]Undefined for video streams.\f[R]
.TP
\f[B]bytesReceived\f[R]
A positive integer that indicates the total number of bytes that have
been received so far for this media source.
.TP
\f[B]concealedSamples\f[R]
A positive integer that indicates the number of samples that had to be
concealed because they were in packets that were lost or arrived too
late to be played out.
\f[I]Undefined for video streams.\f[R]
.TP
\f[B]concealmentEvents\f[R]
A positive integer that indicates the number of concealment events,
where a single event is counted for all consecutive concealed samples
following a non\-concealed sample.
\f[I]Undefined for video streams.\f[R]
.TP
\f[B]estimatedPlayoutTimestamp\f[R] \f[I](experimental)\f[R]
A \f[CR]DOMHighResTimeStamp\f[R] that indicates the estimated playout
time of this receiver\(cqs track.
.TP
\f[B]fecPacketsDiscarded\f[R]
A positive integer value that indicates the number of RTP Forward Error
Correction (FEC) packets which have been received for this source, for
which the error correction payload was discarded.
.TP
\f[B]fecPacketsReceived\f[R]
A positive integer value that indicates the total number of Forward
Error Correction (FEC) packets received for this source.
.TP
\f[B]frameHeight\f[R]
A positive integer that indicates the height of the last decoded frame,
in pixels.
\f[I]Undefined for audio streams and before the first frame is
decoded.\f[R]
.TP
\f[B]framesAssembledFromMultiplePackets\f[R] \f[I](experimental)\f[R]
A positive integer that indicates the total number of correctly decoded
frames for this RTP stream that consist of more than one RTP packet.
\f[I]Undefined for audio streams.\f[R]
.TP
\f[B]framesDecoded\f[R]
A long integer value that indicates the total number of frames of video
which have been correctly decoded so far for this media source.
This is the number of frames that would have been rendered if none were
dropped.
\f[I]Undefined for audio streams.\f[R]
.TP
\f[B]framesPerSecond\f[R]
A positive integer that indicates the number of frames decoded in the
last second.
\f[I]Undefined for audio streams.\f[R]
.TP
\f[B]framesReceived\f[R]
A positive integer that indicates the total number of complete frames
received on this RTP stream.
\f[I]Undefined for audio streams.\f[R]
.TP
\f[B]frameWidth\f[R]
A positive integer that indicates the width of the last decoded frame,
in pixels.
\f[I]Undefined for audio streams and before the first frame is
decoded.\f[R]
.TP
\f[B]freezeCount\f[R] \f[I](experimental)\f[R]
A positive integer that indicates the total number of video freezes
experienced by this receiver.
\f[I]Undefined for audio streams.\f[R]
.TP
\f[B]headerBytesReceived\f[R]
A positive integer that indicates the total number of RTP header and
padding bytes received for this SSRC, including retransmissions.
.TP
\f[B]insertedSamplesForDeceleration\f[R]
A positive integer that indicates the number of samples inserted to slow
playout from the jitter buffer.
\f[I]Undefined for video streams.\f[R]
.TP
\f[B]jitterBufferDelay\f[R]
A number that indicates the accumulated time that all audio samples and
complete video frames have spent in the jitter buffer, in seconds.
.TP
\f[B]jitterBufferEmittedCount\f[R]
A positive integer indicating the total number of audio samples and/or
video frames that have come out of the jitter buffer.
.TP
\f[B]jitterBufferMinimumDelay\f[R]
A number that indicates the minimum delay that might be achieved given
only the network characteristics such as jitter and packet loss.
.TP
\f[B]jitterBufferTargetDelay\f[R]
A number that indicates the accumulated target jitter buffer delay.
.TP
\f[B]keyFramesDecoded\f[R]
A positive integer that indicates the total number of key frames
successfully decoded for this RTP media stream.
\f[I]Undefined for audio streams.\f[R]
.TP
\f[B]lastPacketReceivedTimestamp\f[R]
A \f[CR]DOMHighResTimeStamp\f[R] that indicates the time at which the
last packet was received for this source.
The \f[CR]timestamp\f[R] property, on the other hand, indicates the time
at which the statistics object was generated.
.TP
\f[B]mid\f[R]
A string that uniquely identifies the pairing of source and destination
of the transceiver\(cqs stream.
This is the value of the corresponding \f[CR]RTCRtpTransceiver.mid\f[R]
unless that is null, in which case the statistic property is not
present.
.TP
\f[B]packetsDiscarded\f[R]
A positive integer that indicates the total number of RTP packets
discarded by the jitter buffer due to late or early\-arrival.
.TP
\f[B]pauseCount\f[R] \f[I](experimental)\f[R]
A positive integer that indicates the number of video pauses experienced
by this receiver.
\f[I]Undefined for audio streams.\f[R]
.TP
\f[B]playoutId\f[R] \f[I](experimental)\f[R]
A string that identifies the corresponding
\f[CR]RTCAudioPlayoutStats\f[R] for an audio stream.
\f[I]Undefined for video streams.\f[R]
.TP
\f[B]remoteId\f[R]
A string that identifies the \f[CR]RTCRemoteOutboundRtpStreamStats\f[R]
object that provides statistics for the remote peer for this same SSRC.
This ID is stable across multiple calls to \f[CR]getStats()\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]removedSamplesForAcceleration\f[R]
A positive integer that indicates the number of samples removed from to
speed up playout from the jitter buffer.
\f[I]Undefined for video streams.\f[R]
.TP
\f[B]silentConcealedSamples\f[R]
A positive integer that indicates the number of silent concealed
samples.
\f[I]Undefined for video streams.\f[R]
.TP
\f[B]totalAssemblyTime\f[R] \f[I](experimental)\f[R]
A number that indicates the total time spent assembling successfully
decoded video frames that were transported in multiple RTP packets, in
seconds.
\f[I]Undefined for audio streams.\f[R]
.TP
\f[B]totalAudioEnergy\f[R]
A number that represents the total audio energy of the received track
over the lifetime of the stats object.
\f[I]Undefined for video streams.\f[R]
.TP
\f[B]totalDecodeTime\f[R]
A number that indicates the total time spent decoding frames in this
stream, in seconds.
\f[I]Undefined for audio streams.\f[R]
.TP
\f[B]totalFreezesDuration\f[R] \f[I](experimental)\f[R]
A positive number that indicates the total time that the stream has
spent frozen, in seconds.
\f[I]Undefined for audio streams.\f[R]
.TP
\f[B]totalInterFrameDelay\f[R]
A positive number that indicates the total time spent between
consecutively rendered frames, recorded just after a frame has been
rendered.
\f[I]Undefined for audio streams.\f[R]
.TP
\f[B]totalPausesDuration\f[R] \f[I](experimental)\f[R]
A positive number that indicates the total time that the stream has
spent with paused video, in seconds.
\f[I]Undefined for audio streams.\f[R]
.TP
\f[B]totalProcessingDelay\f[R]
A positive number that indicates the total time spent processing audio
or video samples, in seconds.
.TP
\f[B]totalSamplesDuration\f[R]
A positive number that indicates the total duration of all samples that
have been received, in seconds.
\f[I]Undefined for video streams.\f[R]
.TP
\f[B]totalSamplesReceived\f[R]
A positive integer that indicates the total number of samples received
on this stream.
\f[I]Undefined for video streams.\f[R]
.TP
\f[B]totalSquaredInterFrameDelay\f[R]
A positive number that indicates the sum of the square of inter\-frame
delays between consecutively rendered frames, recorded just after a
frame has been rendered.
\f[I]Undefined for audio streams.\f[R]
.TP
\f[B]trackIdentifier\f[R]
A string that provides the \f[CR]id\f[R] value of the
\f[CR]MediaStreamTrack\f[R] associated with the inbound stream.
.SS Local\-only measurements
These properties are computed locally, and are only available to the
device receiving the media stream.
Their primary purpose is to examine the error resiliency of the
connection, as they provide information about lost packets, lost frames,
and how heavily compressed the data is.
.TP
\f[B]nackCount\f[R]
A number that indicates the number of times the receiver notified the
sender that one or more RTP packets has been lost by sending a Negative
ACKnowledgement (NACK, also called \(lqGeneric NACK\(rq) packet to the
sender.
This value is only available to the receiver.
.TP
\f[B]qpSum\f[R]
A positive integer that provides the sum of the QP values for every
frame decoded by this RTP receiver to date on the video track described
by this statistics object.
\f[I]Valid only for video streams.\f[R]
.SS Statistics measured at the receiver of an RTP stream
These statistics are measured at the receiving end of an RTP stream,
regardless of whether it\(cqs local or remote.
.TP
\f[B]packetsReceived\f[R]
The total number of RTP packets received for this synchronizing source
(SSRC), including retransmissions.
.TP
\f[B]packetsLost\f[R]
The total number of RTP packets lost for this synchronizing source
(SSRC).
Note that this can be negative, as more packets may be received than the
receiver expects.
.TP
\f[B]jitter\f[R]
Packet jitter for this synchronizing source (SSRC), measured in seconds.
.SS Common RTP stream statistics
.TP
\f[B]codecId\f[R]
A string that uniquely identifies the object which was inspected to
produce the \f[CR]RTCCodecStats\f[R] object associated with this RTP
stream.
.TP
\f[B]kind\f[R]
A string that indicates whether the \f[CR]MediaStreamTrack\f[R]
associated with the stream is an audio or a video track.
.TP
\f[B]ssrc\f[R]
The 32\-bit integer that identifies the source of the RTP packets this
object provides.
This value is generated per the RFC 3550 specification.
.TP
\f[B]transportId\f[R]
A string that uniquely identifies the object which was inspected to
produce the \f[CR]RTCTransportStats\f[R] object associated with this RTP
stream.
.SS Common instance properties
The following properties are common to all WebRTC statistics objects.
.TP
\f[B]id\f[R]
A string that uniquely identifies the object that is being monitored to
produce this set of statistics.
.TP
\f[B]timestamp\f[R]
A \f[CR]DOMHighResTimeStamp\f[R] object that indicates the time at which
the sample was taken for this statistics object.
.TP
\f[B]type\f[R]
A string with the value \f[CR]\(dqinbound\-rtp\(dq\f[R], which indicates
the type of statistics that the object contains.
.SH SEE ALSO
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]RTCStatsReport\f[R]
